name: O Técnico Que Veio De Longe

description:
With Cable recuperating on his island haven of Providence, who else can investigate when there is "A Murder in Paradise?" You know who. Say it. Go ahead. Picture it: Deadpool, as a detective, interrogating the most brilliant pacifists on Earth. Monk and Columbo have nothing to fear. Plus: Deadpool is brainwashed by the mysterious group known as the Black Box to become a mindless assassin (which, honestly, didn't take much washing). So Deadpool does what comes naturally to him - the opposite of what's expected! But hey, where's Cable? And what are Cannonball and Siryn doing in the book?

Reprints Cable and Deadpool #13-18.
name: Cable and Deadpool: The Human Race

volume.name: Cable and Deadpool: The Human Race

description: The movie The Empire Strikes Back shows us only a small portion of Luke Skywalker's Jedi training under the tutelage of Master Yoda. In this story, witness a never-before-seen part of that training as Luke is given the task of finding-and retrieving-an object guarded by the deadliest creatures on the swamp world of Dagobah: the monstrous dragonsnakes! This is the most harrowing, dangerous, and muddiest mission that Luke has ever faced! o Luke Skywalker trains to become a Jedi Knight with Master Yoda! The Star Wars Adventures series are parent friendly and perfect for younger readers as well as longtime Star Wars fans.
name: GN

volume.name: Star Wars Adventures: Luke Skywalker And The Treasure Of The Dragonsnakes

description:
Our greed for knowledge recreated his telepathy. Our quest to confine him recreated his telekinesis. He has forged a paradise haven that threatens to destabilize countless governments and religions. One man wants to find out what Cable's intentions are before it's too late. Guest-starring Captain America! Plus: Cable sees the signs -- omens and portents - characters gathering, moving across the board like chess pieces...can Apocalypse be resurrected? Can Cable and Deadpool stop it in time? And most surprising of all...what if one of them doesn't want it to be stopped? And finally, Domino is hired to stop Deadpool's activities in the Central European country of Rumekistan, only to learn he plans to assassinate the country's imposed ruler, the international terrorist named Flag-Smasher. Should she stop him? Will her decision be influenced when she finds out DP was given his mission by...Cable?!    
 
Reprints Cable and Deadpool #25-29.
name: Cable and Deadpool: Living Legends

description: Things are not going so well for either our famously intrepid hero or his 'merry' band of assistant heroes. Spike and Gunn finds themselves committing rooftop shenanigans, Connor is in over his head back at the office, and Angel is starting to wonder if anyone is going to find him before he dies of boredom. And just what is Connor 'chosen' for, anyway?
name: The Trouble With Felicia

description: After recovering her full powers, Illyria sets out to reclaim her position as ruler of the world, seeking her vast army that exists between our plain of existence and has been awaiting her return. Meanwhile, Wesley discovers Gunn's horrifying role in Fred's death and enacts his own kind of justice.
name: Part 4

first_appearance_teams.name: Wolfram and Hart, Attorneys at Law

team_credits.name: Wolfram and Hart, Attorneys at Law

volume.name: Angel: A Hole in the World

description: Where do you hide from a killer, locked in a prison cell? Tensions rise at the Paloverde State Penitentiary as the Predator claims his first victim. Cross gets his assignment to go undercover in the prison and find what he doesn't even believe in.

Cross is closing in on the Predator inside Paloverde State Penetentiary, but what he finds is even more than he bargained for! Action behind bars in the penultimate chapter of the hardest-hitting Predator series yet!

Predator fans, pick up this issue or spend a night in the box! Cross and the other prisoners of Paloverde State Penitentiary come face to face with the creature who hunts them. Break out your riot gear, this is the big one!

The Predator hunts the most dangerous game... man. Now the Predator moves to the most dangerous hunting ground on the planet... the Paloverde State Penitentiary in Arizona. Tension is high in the prison as a convicted serial killer arrives, followed by a Predator bent on killing him and the man chasing them both... Cross. Predator: Race War #1 picks up the action after the three-issue prologue in Dark Horse Presents.

Detective Mike Harrigan goes one-on-one with the killer from outer space, and all the government's special O.W.L. team can do is get in his way! Dark Horse Comics proudly presents the official comic book adaptation of the motion picture sequel to Predator, starring Danny Glover and Rueben Blades.
name: 2 (of 2)

description: Take one remote Alaskan wilderness. Add a lone Forest Ranger, a crazed grizzly, and an unexpected visitor from the stars. Mix well, and you've got a recipe for action. Throw in a forest fire, and you've got Predator: Primal -- the most exciting Predator series to date!

Fleener Creek, Oregon, is a typical, small, Northwestern town -- one that is ready to blow sky high with the repressed emotions in the hearts of the townspeople. And there to light the fuse is one of the most unrepressed killers in the cosmos! A community will either draw together or destroy itself when four kindred spirits are drawn to the forest: an action-starved sheriff, a serial killer, family man Buddy Wilcox, and -- a Predator, the same one who killed Buddy's father right in front of him, in those very woods, thirty years before!

He hails from an unimaginable era: the 31st century. Fleeing through the timestream from the pursuing team of futuristic defenders known as the Guardians of the Galaxy, Korvac the Machine Man has established a secret presence on present-day Earth in the self-created persona of the mysterious Michael. Through such an unassuming guise, Korvac contemplates the elements of a universe he thirsts to command. Yet despite the subtlety of Michael's machinations, the world's greatest super-team -- the mighty Avengers -- catches wind of his cosmos-conquering scheme, thus drawing the two titanic forces into inevitable conflict.
name: HC/TPB
The Graphix Magazine of Postponed Suicides

person_credits.name: Art Spiegelman
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, inker, cover, production

name: The Graphic Aspirin for War Fever
The Graphix Magazine That Overestimates the Taste of the American Public
The Graphix Magazine of Abstract Depressionism
The Graphix Magazine for Your Bomb Shelter's Coffee Table
The Graphix Magazine for Damned Intellectuals

person_credits.name: Art Spiegelman
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, production

name: ...and The Army Pay Roll Plot
A Royal Heritage the Princes of Wales

description: Joint issue by Marvel and Wizard as a teaser before New X-Men started. Contains material from Uncanny X-Men #394 and New X-Men #114.
name: X-Men Pre-Press Edition

description:
Early self-published work by Al Harris & Erik Larsen. 
 
Features a two part story, the first part written & pencilled by Al Harris, and the second part written by Al Harris and pencilled by Erik Larsen.
name: Twilight's Last Gleaming

description: Chandakal the last descendant of the daemons needs a rare gemstone to usher his reign on this universe. But a curse prevents him to acquire the gemstone himself; hence he hires the mafia to steal it! The protector of the gemstone Ninja Kirgi, a Yogic warrior begins his quest to retrieve the stone! Due to confusion, Kirgi believes that Dhruv has masterminded this operation! Dhruv has an arduous task in hand. He needs to pacify Ninja Kirgi at one hand and keep fighting Chandakal and his enhanced magical powers on the other! Dhruv is aptly supported by his friends, Dhanjay and Jingalu! Will the trio be able to stop Chandakal in his evil endeavor or will they get trapped in a mystical world devised by Chandakal? Watch out for Dhruv and his razor sharp wit which is acknowledged by his friends and his opponents alike. It's a battle of the titans fighting for their cause! Read an exciting eased with high paced action!
name: Kirigi ka Kahar

description: The plot deals with the exploits of one of the most lethal enemy Dhruv will ever come across! Chumba is a powerful villain who can control magnetism at will and can disintegrate himself to particles to travel through wires at will! Chumba has blackmailed an officer at Indian missile centre to reveal the where about of a secret mini nuclear battery! After extracting the information Chumba condemns him to a very brutal death! The nuclear device was being transported to the launch site through a goods train. Chumba manages to halt the train on its track. The elite military force is completely paralyzed by the magnetic cuffs which have nailed them to the train. But as fate would have it Dhruv was having a picnic along with Shweta and Natasha and they challenged him to outpace the fateful goods train. Chumba's bid to usurp the nuclear device is foiled by Dhruv! Now Dhruv is a marked man because Chumba needed the nuclear battery to make his missile arsenal functional. When Chumba fails for the second time he gets Shweta kidnapped and dares Dhruv to come and save his sister! Chumba has set a Chakravyuh a multi layered trap for Dhruv where each layer a single exit! Each layer of the trap is guarded by a dangerous and powerful villain! With his sister's life at stake Dhruv is left with no option but to accept the challenge of Chumba! He has to venture into the Chakravyuh set by Chumba and conquer a new villain at every layer. The only solace he can derive from the situation is from the fact that Chandika has promised to protect Shweta from any harm! A battle of epic proportions unfolds exclusively on Raj Comics.
name: Chumba Ka Chakravyuh(Trap Of Chumba)

description: The enthralling adventure is reflective of our present times which can be characterized by a phenomenal growth in crime rate. It appears thatwe are on a self destruct button and our passion for violence has grown to alarming proportions! A series of mindless and brutal assaults is being recorded on camera! What is the rational behind shooting such grotesque incidents? Dhruv tries to get to the bottom of the mystery but he finds that Chandika has been kidnapped and the kidnappers are holding her as a bait to lure Dhruv to fight for a reality show. Dhruv has to walk and fight on a tight rope only to get vanquished from the enemy! His retaliation will lead to Chandika's execution! How will Dhruv wriggle out from this tight corner? This adventure of your favorite super hero which conveys a social message to its readers is available exclusively on Raj Comics.
name: Video Villain

description: The underworld is financed by a shady character named Financer. And when you don't repay your debts to the Financer you have to face the consequences! A band of lunatics are out to kill anyone who refuses to repay their loans to the Financer! Dhruv finds it difficult to nail the mastermind behind the operation as the killers are mentally unfit for interrogation! Perceiving him as a threat the Financer wishes to induct Dhruv into his gang! Will the financer force Dhruv to join his band as his lead henchman? Dhruv is pitted in a mortal combat against the band of lunatic killers who have been set loose to massacre people! Wish him luck and read an unusual adventure exclusively on Raj Comics!
name: Paagak Katilon Ki Toli(Gang of Psycho Killers)

description: Dr. Vargees is a renowned virologist working industriously on a top secret military project! He has managed to obtain a special beta virus which induces a mutation in plants there by helping them to retaliate against attacks just like animals. The mutation increases the strength of these trees manifold, which matches the strength of a battle tank! The beta virus was tested only on plants and its effects on humans were unknown! The beta virus is annexed by Dr. Virus, a brilliant but psychopath scientist who wishes to rule the world by manipulating these viruses. Dr. Virus injects Dr Vargees with the beta virus and escapes from the crime scene. An explosion in the mountain causes an avalanche and the entire laboratory is buried under snow. The death of Dr. Vargees is deemed as an accident just as Dr. Virus had hoped it to be! Dr. Virus tests the beta virus on the humans and unleashes a host of monsters to commit crimes and fund further research work. These monsters have unbelievable strength and are totally under the control of Dr. Virus through a computer chip! One man dares to stand up against his biological warfare and is determined to foil his plans. Dhruv has succeeded in defeating one such monster but will he manage to conquer an entire army! Dhruv is determined to thwart Dr. Virus in his evil plans! He is aptly assisted by Vanputra and the mysterious iceman! The trio unites their strength and wits to stop a powerful and lunatic scientist who has no qualms about unleashing biological warfare on the entire human race! Get hooked to the exciting adventure exclusively on Raj Comics!
name: Doctor Virus

description: Dhruv is having a recurrent nightmare where he finds himself and Natasha trapped among monsters against the backdrop of a volcano! Dhruv is attacked by terrorists followed by a mysterious warrior who wielded a weapon that breathed fire! A look alike of Natasha saves his life and then disappears along with another mysterious warrior who had attacked Dhruv! Perplexed with the sudden appearance and disappearance of the Natasha's look alike, he meets Natasha in her office! Natasha is as clueless as Dhruv and tries to flirt with Dhruv! Dhruv excises restraint and politely postpones a lunch date! Natasha has been assigned by her editor to cover a volcano in the Pacific Ocean! An alarmed and concerned Dhruv volunteers to accompany Natasha. These worst fears come true when he could feel Chandakal's spirit and could see the monsters on the plane! Chandakal is trying to possess the warriors belonging to the mysterious tribe to have access to the pious fire which shall make him extremely powerful! Mahamanav, the futuristic man has awakened from his slumber and is searching for Dhruv who has checkmated him once! The pious fire is guarded by Samri, a warrior who can take orders only from the royal family! Dhruv is having a tough time fighting forces of evil, and saving the innocent. He takes on Chandakal and his cronies, Mahamanav, warriors of a lost tribe and the legendary warrior Samri. Witness the titans battling out against the backdrop of a volcano! The battle royale unfolds exclusively at Raj Comics!
name: Samri Ki Jwala

description: Natasha is falsely implicated in a massacre and her past as has been exposed! Commissioner Rajan has come to know that Natasha is the daughter of Grand Master Robo the dreaded terrorist! Natasha has turned into a fugitive and blames Dhruv for this debacle! Dhruv manages to locate Natasha and asks her to surrender! The police are informed of Natasha's whereabouts and they arrest her! Can Dhruv seek justice for Natasha? Introducing the bold and sexy siren, Black Cat! Who is this Mysterious fighter? What is her role in this grand conspiracy?? It's an adventure with unexpected twists and turns and high on adrenalin to satisfy your senses! Who was responsible for this massacre and why was Natasha implicated? Let the conspiracy unfold exclusively on Raj Comics.
name: Black Cat

description: The conspiracy has been exposed but it's too late! Grand master Robo wanted his daughter back and got her falsely implicated in a public massacre! Black cat has kidnapped Natasha from the high security prison and hurls a bomb at Dhruv! Dhruv has been grievously injured and is battling death in the hospital! Black Cat has delivered to Natasha to Grand Master Robo and in return has been promoted as deputy commander of his army. Robo dreams of his daughter Natasha commanding his army once again! Natasha feels greatly aggrieved that she was treated shoddily by the law! Will Natasha revert back to her formal life and retaliate against the injustice that had been metted out to her? Black Cat's history is unfolded in the concluding part of the story! Who will thwart Robo in his evil designs once Dhruv has been eliminated? An adventure with a very befitting and captivating climax exclusively on Raj Comics!
name: Robo Ka Pratisodh

description: A new menace is engulfing the town of Rajnagar. An alien is killing its residents just to steal their soul. A dreaded terrorist organization named Killer League has taken a contract of abducting Saikal Saxon, a famous rock star! Its members manage to interrupt his show at Rajnagar and hold him as hostage! The terrorists demand for a helicopter and twenty crores in lieu of releasing Saikal Saxon! Dhruv rescues Saikal Saxon but the terrorists manage to escape law enforcement officials. The alien tries stealing the soul of Saikal Saxon but is unable to do so due to fault in his machinery. The alien forces a thief to steal a component from the space centre at Rajnagar. Despite the replacement of the component the machine is still not functioning optimally. Hence the alien is forced to join hands with the Killer League. He hires the gang to slaughter people enabling him to capture their soul. Dhruv in hot pursuit of Killer League and the mysterious alien! But can Dhruv stop this mayhem? The killer leagues have failed to abduct Saikal Saxon and need to repay the initial advance they received for the assignment. The alien has paid them beyond their expectations to massacre the high profile personalities! But can they manage to defeat their nemesis? Get hooked to an enjoyable adventure exclusively at Raj Comics
name: Atma Ke Chor(Hijackers of Soul)

description: Dr. Bhama, a research scientist working at the prestigious atomic centre is shoved from the seventh floor of the picturesque building. Dhruv tried to break his fall but Dr. Bhama was grievously injured! Dr. Bhama manages to warn Dhruv about a spy in the organization! Dhruv confronts the spy which leads to a mortal combat! In a freak accident, the spy is killed by a steel boomerang! The director discloses to Dhruv that a secret atomic explosion is being conducted at Pokhran! Dhruv recalls that his father, Commissioner Rajan was asked to take charge of security at Pokhran! Shweta, her sister had accompanied Commissioner Rajan to his new posting! The spy network had managed to obtain the designs of nuclear device and wanted to sabotage the explosion! They had discovered secret passages which lead them to the site of explosion! The explosion was sabotaged and the army was swung into action. The entire region was cordoned off and the search for the saboteurs was in progress! Chandika was found unconscious under mysterious circumstances near the site of explosion! The needle of suspicion was pointing towards both Chandika and Commissioner Rajan who was vouching for her! Dhruv volunteers for the investigation and gets the nod from the army! After the explosion nuclear scientists and their assistants were being bitten by vampire. The infected persons later turned into vampires with super human strength! Dhruv had a haunch that the old fort near the site of explosion held the key to this puzzle! Menacing vampires, a hooded mysterious figure, a comatose Chandika and scrupulous terrorists add a lot of spice to the adventure! Watch Dhruv annihilate the evil forces exclusively on Raj Comics!
name: Vampire

description: The swamp at the out skirts of Raj Nagar has been the graveyard of many a criminals! While on a rescue mission Dhruv spots a plane of foreign origin being shot down by another of the same origin! This incident could be a breach of national security! Mysterious cylinders fall in the swamp and a new mutant evolves in the swamp. It has gone berserk and so have the trees, which are causing havoc in Raj Nagar! Dhruv is baffled by the origin of the new mutant and the crazy behavior of the trees! The mutant is out to convert the entire town into a swamp! What is the mystery behind these cylinders and the planes? Will Dhruv get to the root of this problem and find the way out before Rajnagar disappears in a swamp? Read a mystifying adventure exclusively on Raj Comics!
name: Daldal(Quick Sand)

description: Dhruv is on hot pursuit of a drug paddling syndicate! But a mutant is out to seek her revenge from the same! She is a law unto herself and is ready to eliminate Dhruv to extract her revenge. She acknowledges herself as Lady Bird! Lady Bird has already made two unsuccessful attempts in wiping off Dhruv! Dhruv is having a tough time dodging killer hawks carrying dynamite pellets! But Dhruv is determined to uphold law and order in the town. It's a battle of will and nerves between two gifted persons who seek justice but their opinion defers on the means to acquire it. Will Dhruv solve the mystery of the mutant? Can he stop Lady Bird from taking the law into her own hands? This action packed adventure is available exclusively on Raj Comics.
name: Udti Maut(Flying Death)

description: Chandakal's astral body has been blown into pieces by Mahamanav while his physical body is on display in Swarn Nagri the city of gold. Dhruv has an ominous feeling about the display and advises against it. But Dhanjay does not pay heed to Dhruv's warnings! As fate would have it these bits integrate into three distinct pieces. These pieces begin to possess human bodies and ushers uncharacteristic changes in their behavior! Now these pieces are about to unite and set free the physical body of Chandakal. Dhruv is determined to prevent the inevitable but can he? A riveting adventure of Dhruv exclusively on Raj Comics! The astral body of the last surviving daemon is about to set free it's physical self! Will the devil succeed in his Endeavour?
name: Chandkaal Ki Wapasi

description: Kankaltantra is a fierce warrior who travels across the ages and challenges its undisputed champion warrior to a duel! And he comes to Raj Nagar to challenge Dhruv, but to his dismay Dhruv has been murdered under mysterious circumstances! The news of Dhruv's death has been suppressed in the media. With every super villain claiming to have killed Dhruv it is difficult to find the truth! Kankaltantra has summoned a conclave of super villains to ascertain the identity of the super villain who managed to conquer Dhruv! Kankaltantra has analyzed that there existed eight super villains who could have killed Dhruv. He personally invites them to the conclave with Grand Master Robo being the last entrant! Kankaltantra, promises vast amount to the super villain responsible for Dhruv's death! The eight participants to this conclave were Dhwani Raj, Chandakal, Suprema, Bauna Vaman, Dr. Virus, Chumba, Black Cat and Grand Master Robo! Kankaltantra has appointed Biotron a robot with advanced artificial intelligence to examine the claims of these super villains! With a greedy intent, each super villain claims to have killed Dhruv in the most bizarre fashion. The super villain had to pace penetrative questions from Biotron who was punching holes in their testimony! The first testimony was that of Dhwani Raj who claimed to have killed Dhruv at the space training center. So is he destined to be crowned as the super villain and rule the world? Or is it one of the other villains who shall bask in glory? Read this thrilling inquest exclusively on Raj Comics!
name: Maine Maara Dhruva Ko

description: A conclave to determine the murderer of Dhruv has been convened by Kankaltantra a legendary warrior! He has promised great riches and great powers to the one who has finally managed to conquer Dhruv! Already the conclave has heard the testimony of Dhwani Raj, Bauna Vaman and Black Cat. Biotron the robot with artificial intelligence has rubbished their claims and they have left the conclave in disgrace! Now it's up to the rest of the participants to stake their claim to glory! The conclave resumes its deliberation with Dr. Virus presenting his claim! He claimed to have slain Dhruv, Samri, and Dr. Varghese in a combat! Biotron produces Samri and Dr. Varghese as witness to negate his claim! Chumba gets cold feet before his testimony and concedes that he did not kill Dhruv and was attending this conclave to try his luck! That left Chandakal, Supreme and grand master Robo as the probable villains responsible for Dhruv's death! So which shall be crowned as the super villain after proving that he had slain Dhruv? Will he get to rule this world or is there another twist to the tale? Watch Biotron examine the claims of super villains with a razor sharp wit and intelligence! But will he finally announce the winner of this conclave!
name: Hatyara Kaun

description: The savage she-demon and charter member of the Femforce in her first solo book, this one-shot anolmaly gave readers more insight into the ancient evil cat-diety Sehkmet, who posseses She-cat and fuels her powers. The rest of the origin story herin was later refuted as a ruse, and the true details of 'Cat's beginnings were eventually chronicled in Femforce Up Close #4. But this entertaining piece of fiction(not considered to be part of official Femforce continuity) was written by James Misson, and pencilled by Larry(Rock Comics) Nadolsky, with finishes by Mark Propst, Billie Marimon and Bill Black. Also contains a humorous two-pager where She-cat comes to visit AC editor/publisher Bill Black .
name: Curse Of The She-Cat

description: Cover by Vic Brigdes!! Yankee Girl stars in this continuation of events stated in Femforce Up Close #11, as YG’s ill-fated attempt to permanently return to her glory days of the 1940′s has her altering events in the past involving evil genius Bartholomew Watson and a doomsday weapon, brings her into combat with Imperial Japan’s WW II era female powerhouse Divine Wind, and in the end teachers her the true meaning of being a heroine. Story by Mark Heike, with art by Dave Roberts and Chris Allen. (Note: this entire story was leter reprinted as part of the Femforce: Timestorm graphic novel. 24 pages, black & white with color covers. 8 1/2″ X 5 3/4″, saddle stiched.
The conclusion to this five part story. Morningstar and Cyberdata's plan is revealed. Cyberforce and Hunter Killer teams comes together to stop them.

Detective Schaefer has been having bizarre nightmares of a nasty-looking, seven-foot-tall, alien headhunter. One big problem: Schaefer is wide awake. And though he's been hardened by the atrocities he's experienced as a NYC cop, it won't prepare him for his fateful, savage confrontation with the Predator he thought he'd destroyed years ago. Now his search for his brother Dutch may end with no answers, more questions, and a lot more bloodshed.

Though Predators are natural-born killers, one theory suggests they have a code of honor. Leave it to NYPD Detective Schaefer to find a Predator that doesn't share that theory. Deep in the heart of South America, Schaefer is hunting for a piece of his past -- his lost brother Dutch -- while another piece of his past -- a Predator he thought long dead -- stalks him through the dense, sweltering jungle. And when they finally lock horns, the "dark river" will run red!

Detective Shaefer has traded the concrete jungle of New York for the sweaty hell of its South American counterpart. He's on a mission to find his missing brother, but he's going to be hard pressed to do that. Someone is luring Shaefer into an inevitable confrontation with a Predator. One that he's faced before. One that he thought he killed. One that wants revenge.
An angry grizzly! A raging forest fire! A bloodthirsty Predator! And a Forest Ranger who's feeling way out of her league!

Fleener Creek was a sleepy old town all right -- like Andy and Barney could have walked right down Main Street on their way to fetch a slice of Aunt Bee's apple pie. But sleepy towns aren't always so dreamy. Sometimes sleep brings on nightmares, the kind that begin and end with an eight-foot-tall monster wielding spears and knives and all sorts of weapons. Fleener Creek may have been sleepy, but most of the folks in this town won't sleep sound again, not for a very long time. And others will never again wake up.

The sleepy town of Fleener Creek isn't so sleepy anymore. Young Sheriff Kelly is on the trail of a psychopathic killer, while Buddy Wilcox hunts the forest for his childhood obsession, a monster the other townsfolk believe exists only in his imagination -- a Predator. The dark underbelly of this little community has finally been exposed, and, like raw flesh hitting sunlight for the first time, it's going to burn.

A small northwestern town's heart of darkness is laid bare when evil comes to call! McCutcheon is a serial killer who finds himself no longer the hunter, but the hunted, as the authorities and some . . . thing chase him through the forest. Kelly Mathis is a small-town sheriff who must face old fears as she encounters the "boogieman" of her childhood. Buddy Wilcox is a family man whose father's brutal slaying still haunts him years later. Thirty years ago, a Predator came to town. Now these four kindred spirits are drawn together, toward an explosive conclusion!

name: Land of the Pygmy Indians

description: Naturalist Maya Bergstrom and ex-combat photographer George Maxwell have just met a Predator for the first time -- an ancient, legendary warrior unlike any other Predator. But he's not here to hunt humans. His mission is to bring down three young, thrill-kill Predators that don't follow their race's warrior code. But Maya and George are on to something: the real reason Predators are flocking to Earth. If they're right, the human race is in for one hell of a wake-up call!

When Predators clash with other Predators, look out! It all comes to a head as the ancient, mysterious Predator warrior faces off against the young, merciless trio of his race. Will discipline and experience win out against youth and raw power? And what of Maya Bergstrom's chilling hypothesis that Predators were Earth's original inhabitants eons ago?! The answers will shock you!

In the heart of Yellowstone National Park, terrifying events are unfolding . A trio of thrill-kill Predators has been using Earth as their own private slaughterhouse. However, these killers don't realize that they are being hunted by one of their own: a noble but deadly warrior who is the granddaddy of all Predators! But, as this death match comes to a boil, a nameless government agent has his own plans for this otherwordly race.

In the dense wilderness of Yellowstone National Park, a photojournalist named George witnesses the carnage brought on by three young renegade Predators. Mya, a naturalist, has stumbled across a noble elder of this alien race, every bit as tough. Its purpose is a mystery to her but soon becomes clear: As the renegades mercilessly carve a wake of death, they are unaware that one of their own has come to Earth to hunt them.

"Too Tall" Tara debuts, as our favorite ecologist-turned-jungle girl has gained the power to grow into a giantess! (GTS fans, take note!)Helping producer Mike Frankovich, Jr. with special effects on a new T. V. series, the oversized jungle queen manages to tame an eleven-foot gorilla in "My Heart Belongs To Kong", written by Bill Black, drawn by Dick(Giant-Man)Ayers, and inked by Black and Mark Heike. And, the all-time most popular jungle girl, Fiction House's Sheena makes her JG debut this issue, in an untitled 1940's vintage stary drawn by Robert H. Webb and friends, shot directly from the ACTUAL ORIGINAL ART!! Then, it's two more Fiction House Golden Age classics, a Matt Baker-drawn Tiger Girl from Fight Comics, and Bob(Long Sam)Lubbers on Camilla, Wild Girl Of The Congo, from Jungle Comics. Plus photos and a letter from T. V.'s original Sheena. pinup favorite Irish McCalla.

While the survivors of the Occupation get a closer look at the Church of the Cosmos' religious fervor, including entrance to their otherworldly temple, Susanne is singled out by Spock to be tested. But will Spock's gift to her truly be an ascension or a curse?
name: The Gift

description: There's a legend down in Bayou Lafourche of a man turned into a monster. Well, legends aren't always fiction, and monsters aren't always horrible, but something's got to account for the bodies being pulled out of that swamp. And that something's got nothing to do with voodoo.

Based on the anticipated series from Warner Bros. TV premiering on Fox this January! Christopher Chance, the Human Target, has undertaken a deadly mission to protect an informant against organized crime families while he collects evidence throughout Europe. Unfortunately, the mob's next stop is at the Vatican. Can even Chance's considerable skills get them inside the holiest and most heavily guarded of locales?
name: The Wanted: Extremely DEAD Contract!, Clause Two: The Vatican Rag!

description: Beautiful, buxom babes in futuristic, far-out sci-fi adventure featuring some of the best "good girl art" ever done in comics!! See Stormy Tempest, the bountiful bounty hunter best arch-villainesses Polly Vinyl and Leatheretta in a girl-fight spectacular by Bill Black, John Beatty and Steve Vance. Then, the glamorous heroines from Fiction House's Planet Comics unite to battle evil in bikinis, lingerie and leather as The Star Fems- by Bill Black and Marc Hempel.This reprises material originally seen in the long-out-of-print Paragon Publications classic from 1980, Star Fems #1. Plus, a vintage reprint of actual Golden Age material that inspired ST, (straight out of Planet Comics of the 1940's) Mysta of the Moon by Reuben Moriera.
